Let's implement the fix by checking both the short and long option strings:

public void setSelected(Option option) throws AlreadySelectedException {
    if (option == null) {
        selected = null;
        return;
    }
    // check if the same option is already selected
    String opt = option.getOpt();
    String longOpt = option.getLongOpt();
    if (selected == null || selected.equals(opt) || (longOpt != null && selected.equals(longOpt))) {
        selected = opt;
    } else {
        throw new AlreadySelectedException(this, option);
    }
}

This is minimal and fixes the bug where the same option might be represented by its long option. But if the option itself is different but has the same short option, that's a different scenario (two different options with the same short option? That's not allowed). So this fix should work.

